    {
      "id": "el_17",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 535,
      "y": 434,
      "width": 351,
      "height": 234,
      "text": "Proposition  | Subject | Predicate\nAll S are P  |   YES   |    NO\nNo S are P   |   YES   |   YES\nSome S are P |   NO    |    NO\nSome S not P |   NO    |   YES\n\nUniversal → Subject distributed\nNegative  → Predicate distributed\n\nWHY: \"Distributed\" = the term covers ALL its\n  members. Universal talks about all S;\n  negative excludes all P.\n\nEx: \"All dogs are animals\" → dogs=distributed\n  (all dogs), animals=not (only some animals)",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 1700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 17,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Proposition  | Subject | Predicate\nAll S are P  |   YES   |    NO\nNo S are P   |   YES   |   YES\nSome S are P |   NO    |    NO\nSome S not P |   NO    |   YES\n\nUniversal → Subject distributed\nNegative  → Predicate distributed\n\nWHY: \"Distributed\" = the term covers ALL its\n  members. Universal talks about all S;\n  negative excludes all P.\n\nEx: \"All dogs are animals\" → dogs=distributed\n  (all dogs), animals=not (only some animals)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
